Singleton ensures only one instance of a class exists throughout the application lifecycle.Use cases:
    Database connection pools
    Configuration managers
    Logger instances
    Cache managers
    Thread pools

When To Create Singleton?
    Shared resource access
    Heavy object initialization
    Global state management
    Stateless utility services

Built-in Singletons in Java & Spring Boot
Java:
    Runtime.getRuntime()
    System class internals
    Collections.EMPTY_LIST

Spring Boot:
    Every @Bean, @Service, @Repository, @Component is singleton-scoped by default
    ApplicationContext itself is a singleton

